                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\">\n                <placeName>\n                    <sic>Sanfrancisco</sic>\n                </placeName>\n                <date>March 30th 1864</date>\n            </p>\n            <p>\n                <addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">\n                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>\n            </p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(3)\">My dear Sir</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(5)\">Herewith I<lb/> send you a copy of my Discourses. I shall<lb/> be\n                happy to have you review it, as I know<lb/> it will be ably and impartially done. I\n                would<lb/> willingly have sent you some copies for sale, but<lb/> the price is too\n                high. I published 1500 copies<lb/> which cost me <hi rend=\"underline\">700 dollars\n                    in-Gold</hi>. They are<lb/> sold here for 1 Dollar pr copy. If you should<lb/>\n                think well of it and could affect a sale in the<lb/> states we might talk of your\n                publishing them<lb/> yourself for the states. <hi rend=\"underline\">I think I shall\n                    sell one</hi><lb/>\n                <hi rend=\"underline\">thousand Copies here</hi>. The Book is well received<lb/> here,\n                all the press have noticed it favorably except<lb/> the “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >Gleaner</hi>” which no doubt you have seen<lb/> The “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >Hebrew</hi>” I think will succeed. The Messenger<lb/> of <placeName>New\n                    York</placeName> sympathizes with the “<hi rend=\"underline\">Gleaner</hi>”<lb/>\n                in consequence of the appearance of the “Hebrew”<lb/> which I consider out of place.\n                What is your opinion?<lb/>\n                <persName>Mr Frank</persName> of <placeName>New York</placeName> is here, and on his\n                return<lb/> to <placeName>New York</placeName> wishes to publish my Class Book as\n                the<lb/> whole Edition has been consumed. He will do so<lb/> in his own\n                responsibility, as the price is too high here.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw58426/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
