          "annotations": [
            {
              "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw58426/canvas/p2/annopage",
              "type": "AnnotationPage",
              "items": [
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw58426/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p>I suppose you have considered that I have<lb/> neglected in not writing to you the\n                fact is that<lb/> very little has <sic>traspired</sic> here worth troubling<lb/>\n                you. What has <sic>occured</sic> you can learn from<lb/> the “Hebrew” and “Gleaner”\n                I do not write for the<lb/> Gleaner, but I do for the “<hi rend=\"underline\"\n                    >Hebrew</hi>” from which<lb/> you can copy the several items. I am anxious<lb/>\n                to see the Hebrew succeed, although I am not<lb/> interested in the same from any\n                pecuniary benefit<lb/> as the “Gleaner” would make you believe.<lb/> The fact is it\n                is jealous and envious and<lb/> wishes to grasp every thing—and I do not\n                endorse<lb/> such mercenary motives such does not form<lb/> any part of my\n                character. And therefore I do<lb/> try and assist the “Hebrew” such a paper\n                being<lb/> wanted in the <placeName>Pacific Coast</placeName>. A new society<lb/> is\n                being formed here entitled “The Universal<lb/> Jewish Alliance” to cooperate with\n                the Central<lb/> Committee in <placeName>Paris, France</placeName>. <sic>full</sic>\n                particulars<lb/> you will find published in the “<hi rend=\"underline\">Hebrew</hi>”\n                so that<lb/> I need not trouble you with writing it now.<lb/> I have had but little\n                success disposing<lb/> of your Books, I shall however immediately<lb/> after\n                    <add>פסח</add> make up my account and forward<lb/> you what I have in hand, and\n                my own <sic>indebtness</sic><lb/> for your publications. Your Occident I read\n                with<lb/> pleasure, it is the only periodical among our people<lb/> which contains\n                any thing worth reading.</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kw58426/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
